pageContext.claim: “You have many countries, don't do any testing, so they don't have any cases. You have many, many countries that have very few cases, 'cause they don't do testing.”
pageContext.analysis: Some countries may not have great testing protocols, but that does not mean they do not have cases. They just have cases that have not been identified. When the Trump administration bungled testing at the start of the pandemic, it gave a false picture of how the disease had spread through the country.
